Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British chicken breasts{2} into a #medium bowl{}. Add a drizzle of oil, half the garlic and half the @roasted spice and herb blend{2%sachets}.

Add a good squeeze of lemon juice, season with salt and pepper and mix together so the chicken is nicely coated. Lay the chicken onto one side of another large baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Alternatively, BBQ the chicken if you'd prefer.

Meanwhile, in another #large bowl{}, combine a good squeeze of lemon juice with the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

Add the cucumber and tomatoes to the dressing. Crumble in half the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} and toss together. Set aside.

In another large bowl, combine the @breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, remaining garlic and remaining roasted spice and herb blend.

Add the @lamb mince{200%g} and crumble in the remaining Greek style salad cheese. Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Shape into mini sausage shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the chicken is about halfway through cooking, remove the tray from the oven, add the koftas to the other side and pop back into the oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Alternatively, BBQ the koftas if you'd prefer.

Meanwhile, spoon the @houmous{100%g} into a #serving bowl{}. Drizzle over a little olive oil and set aside.

When everything's ready, drizzle the @honey{15%g} over the chicken, turning to coat it in the sticky glaze. Transfer to your plates along with the koftas.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Serve the wedges, salad and houmous alongside, as well as any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Add a dollop of @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} for dipping. Enjoy!